Given the clock time in string format &ldquo;xx:xx&rdquo; as the input, e.g. &ldquo;22:12&rdquo;, find the closest clock time which is larger than the input time. All the inputs are valid.
Example 1 Input: &ldquo;22:12&rdquo;
Output: &ldquo;22:21&rdquo;
Example 2: Input: &ldquo;13:09&rdquo;
Output: &ldquo;19:03&rdquo;
Example 3: Input: &ldquo;23:59&rdquo;
Output: &ldquo;23:59&rdquo;
Explanation: Since there is no time larger than &ldquo;23:59&rdquo;, we return the original time.
